Static Block : "A block which is declared inside the class block and pre-fix with an static modifier is know as the static block ."

points :
        1) A static block dose not have any name.
        2) A static block does not have any acess modifier.
        3) A static block does not have any return type
        4) A static block dose not have any formal argument.

Syntax :

        class callsname
          {
              static
                {

                }
          }


Simple basic code  :  

                  class StaticMethod1 
                {
                	static 
                	{
                		System.out.println("From the static block 1");
                	}
                		
                	public static void main(String[] args) 
                	{
                		System.out.println("Hello World!");
                	}
                	
                	static 
                	{
                		System.out.println("Form the static block 2");
                	}
                }



